"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-eileen-gu-alex-ferreira-us-grand-prix-copper-mountain-ski-halfpipe-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Alex Ferreira and Eileen Gu capped their 2024 dominance by winning the Toyota U.S. Grand Prix at Copper Mountain, Colorado, on Saturday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferreira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Ferreira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferreira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Ferreira\"}, {\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eileen Gu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\"}, {\"begin\": 71, \"end\": 77, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Racing_(Formula_One_team)\", \"score\": 0.9986303142260512, \"rank\": 0.0012123760297804952, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Racing_(Formula_One_team)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Racing_(Formula_One_team)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ferreira, a two-time Olympic medalist, took the men's final with a 94.75-point second run that included two 1620s.\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was joined on the podium by Canadian Brendan Mackay (91.25) and American Nick Goepper (89.25).\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9976759978179752, \"rank\": 0.0021570581688810874, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendan_Mackay\", \"score\": 0.9999979746680812, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brendan Mackay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendan_Mackay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brendan_Mackay\"}, {\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9958190336061065, \"rank\": 0.004060732894684516, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Goepper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nick Goepper\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Goepper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Goepper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ferreira won all seven of his competitions in the 2023-24 season, then was runner-up to Mackay and Goepper in the first two World Cups of this season.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\", \"score\": 0.9669927321976728, \"rank\": 0.019246440276650494, \"text\": \"Mackay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ken_Mackay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Aspen, Colorado, native seeks 2026 Olympic gold after silver and bronze at the last two Games.\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 516, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Buffaloes\", \"score\": 0.7837975942110604, \"rank\": 0.21502415144775566, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Buffaloes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Buffaloes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just hungry,\\\" Ferreira said.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want it.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I want to win the Olympics, and I want to do it not only for my town, for my state, for my country.\\\"\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gu, who in 2022 won two gold medals and one silver at a home Olympics in China, won the Copper Mountain women's title with a 90.50-point first run featuring two 900s.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9912341540898307, \"rank\": 0.006706499394290377, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It help up, barely, over later runs from Brit Zoe Atkin (89.75) and Canadian Cassie Sharpe (89.00).\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Atkin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zoe Atkin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Atkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Atkin\"}, {\"begin\": 990, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9976759978179752, \"rank\": 0.0021570581688810874, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sharpe, the 2018 Olympic gold medalist, is returning from August 2023 childbirth.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Bowdler_Sharpe\", \"score\": 0.9800407031712017, \"rank\": 0.020354087287251087, \"text\": \"Sharpe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Bowdler_Sharpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Bowdler_Sharpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gu fell while landing the last trick of her third and final run but walked off on her own power.\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old earned a 17th career World Cup victory, breaking her tie with Frenchwoman Tess Ledeux for the most among male and female freeskiers.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tess_Ledeux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tess Ledeux\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tess_Ledeux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tess_Ledeux\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gu was last beaten in a top-level ski halfpipe final in March 2021.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the 2022 Olympics, she returned to classes at Stanford, plus has also studied at Oxford, leading to a lack of recent time on snow.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9983543386443717, \"rank\": 0.0016232293013863609, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}, {\"begin\": 1509, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.9971039646596361, \"rank\": 0.0026542260195236036, \"text\": \"Oxford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want to be a lot better than I am now,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am happy to have sneaked out with a win, but I want to win by a lot more.\\\"\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copper Mountain Grand Prix highlights air Sunday from 4:30-6 p.m.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET on NBC andPeacock.\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9996346477167154, \"rank\": 0.0003542788422269361, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1783, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999851390841, \"rank\": 1.486087636279896e-08, \"text\": \"A Division\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DISCLAIMER: This site and the products offered are for entertainment purposes only, and there is no gambling offered on this site.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This service is intended for adult audiences.\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No guarantees are made for any specific outcome.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, please call 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2114, \"entitie